Model Armor (GCP) — AI Security & Guardrails

Model Armor is a managed AI security layer on Google Cloud that helps protect generative AI applications from misuse, data leakage, and malicious inputs.

Core Guardrails & Protections:
==============================
Prompt Injection Protection : Detects and blocks prompt injection attacks designed to override system instructions or manipulate model behavior.
Malicious Input Detection: Filters prompts containing harmful, unsafe, or policy-violating content before they reach the model.
Sensitive Data Protection: identifies and helps prevent exposure of sensitive information (e.g., secrets, credentials, PII) in both prompts and responses.
Model Misuse Prevention: Enforces safeguards against attempts to repurpose models for disallowed or high-risk use cases.
Centralized Enforcement: Applies consistent AI security policies across all applications and workloads using generative models.
Audit & Monitoring Support: Provides visibility into blocked requests, policy violations, and threat patterns for security review and compliance reporting.
Reduces Data Exfiltration Risk: Helps prevent attackers from extracting system prompts, proprietary logic, or internal data via model interactions.
